==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tipple
<hw>Tip"ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Tippled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Tippling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[From
<ets>tip</ets> a small end, or a word akin to it; cf. Norw.
<ets>tipla</ets> to tipple, to drip, Prov. E. <ets>tip</ets>,
<ets>tiff</ets>, <ets>tift</ets>, a draught of liquor, dial. G.
<ets>zipfeln</ets> to eat and drink in small parts. See <er>Tip</er> a
point, and cf. <er>Tipsy</er>.]</ety> <def>To drink spirituous or strong
liquors habitually; to indulge in the frequent and improper used of
spirituous liquors; especially, to drink frequently in small quantities,
but without absolute drunkeness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Few of those who were summoned left their homes, and those few
generally found it more agreeable to <qex>tipple</qex> in alehouses than
to pace the streets.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tipple</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tipple
<hw>Tip"ple</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To drink, as strong
liquors, frequently or in excess.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Himself, for saving charges,⟦br⟧
A peeled, sliced onions eats, and <qex>tipples</qex> verjuice.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To put up in bundles in order to dry, as
hay.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tipple</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Tipple
<hw>Tip"ple</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Liquor taken in tippling;
drink.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Pulque, the national <qex>tipple</qex> of Mexico.</q> <rj><qau>S.
B. Griffin.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tipple</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Tipple
<hw>Tip"ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. 3d
<er>Tip</er>.]</ety> <def>An apparatus by which loaded cars are emptied
by tipping; also, the place where such tipping is done.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tippled</ent>⟦br⟧
